altitudeMap

Class AltitudeMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • altitudeMap.AltitudeMap

  • public class AltitudeMap
extends java.lang.Object
    AltitudeMap. The class contains a grid map with altitude information. The altitudes are saved in the double 2d-array altitudes[y][x] with y signifying the row and x signifying the column. All other attributes are metadata.

        public AltitudeMap(java.lang.String filename,
                   int ncols,
                   int nrows,
                   double xllcorner,
                   double yllcorner,
                   double cellsize,
                   double NODATA_value,
                   double[][] altitudes)
        Creates new AltitudeMap.
        Parameters:
        filename - Name of map file
        ncols - Number of columns
        nrows - Number of rows
        xllcorner - X-coordinate (etrs-tm35fin) of the map's lower left hand corner
        yllcorner - Y-coordinate (etrs-tm35fin) of the map's lower left hand corner
        cellsize - Map cell size in meters
        NODATA_value - Value used for missing altitude data in the map
        altitudes - Altitudes of [y][x]-points on the map with (0,0) top left corner.
